Tamary Chikiwa in BULAWAYO TALENTED young filmmaker, Ntobikamama Moyo has penned two novels as she seeks to diversify her passion for the arts. Moyo, whose two films Gold Diggers and $400 were aired on Zambezi Magic, has published two novels titled Another Wedding and In 30 Days which lean towards romance and friendship. Moyo told the Daily News that she is discovering that she is both a scriptwriter and novelist evidenced by her intimacy with the pen and paper. “I really never have to choose one over the other because both are exciting and my passion. Achieving balance between the two is quite easy because the writing and publishing of a single novel is a long process where’s script writing is swift especially if I am collaborating with different film producers. “The challenge is when I have to choose what to do with a story idea—should I expand the concept and make it a novel or should I microwave it into a movie script?” Moyo said. In her novel, In 30 Days, the scribe questions the significance of duration of romantic relationships when one is determined to settle for marriage. Against the ideal situation where society believes in years of dating and knowing each other, Moyo places the idea of love in 30 days. “I tried to explore the idea of friendship, betrayal, forgiveness and trust, but what I really wanted to stand out was that time is subjective and not a one-size fits all when it comes to matters of the heart. “I wanted to create a heart-warming story for people who love,” she said.  Moyo said the current Covid-19 lockdown has given her ample time to diversify hence she penned these books driven by her taste for romance. “During lockdown, I found myself with some time on my hands and I dedicated it to publishing a book. “In 30 Days is basically a book about Anna Ndebele, who is dumped by Khwezi Khumalo after a nine-year relationship. “Heartbroken and in need of some serious closure, she attends his wedding and meets an interesting character in the body of Herndel Jones and in 30 days, Anna has to fight for her happiness,” she said. Her other novel, Another Wedding which was a collaboration with friends from university has since been adopted into a feature film by producer Kudzai Chikomo. Sponsored Links

    
      
        
          
